0 0 M(Source: )show(_KY Contra Tunes_ and thesession.org/tunes/15717 for the base)show
0 -14.52 T
0 0 M(Notes: )show(Now this is an interesting number! The B-part follows a pretty standard I/VIIb)show
0 -12.10 T
42.49 0 M (progression found in many Celtic tunes, but the A-part uses the "Dorian vamp,")show
0 -12.10 T
42.49 0 M (pretty unusual in fiddle tunes but a staple in classic rock. For that reason, I)show
0 -12.10 T
42.49 0 M (think it's perhaps a more "jammy" tune than a melodic one; and one version I)show
0 -12.10 T
42.49 0 M (looked at had a G-F-Em-Am windup that gave it a little more of a bluesy punch.)show
0 -12.10 T
42.49 0 M (The top 4 bars are the tune in its base form, and the bottom 4 bars illustrate)show
0 -12.10 T
42.49 0 M (how I imagine the tune in a jam setting.)show
0 -14.52 T
